# =============================================================================
# DCENT_OS out-of-band build-inputs manifest
# =============================================================================
#
# These files are REQUIRED to build DCENT_OS firmware from a clean checkout
# but are deliberately NOT in git (gitignored: extracted/proprietary Bitmain
# and BraiinsOS boot components plus the Linaro toolchain tarball — they are
# not redistributable under this repo's licenses).
#
# A clean checkout (fresh local clone OR CI/GitHub runner) MUST be populated
# with these files before running build-dcentrald.sh / build_in_docker.sh.
# Use the sibling script:
#
#     sh DCENT_OS_Antminer/scripts/provision_build_inputs.sh
#
# which copies each entry from an out-of-band source directory and verifies
# it against the SHA256 recorded here (fail-closed supply-chain gate).
#
# FORMAT: identical to `sha256sum` output — one entry per line:
#     <sha256-hex64>  <path relative to repo root>
# Lines starting with '#' and blank lines are ignored.
# Verify by hand from the repo root with:  sha256sum -c <this file> --quiet
# (comment lines make GNU sha256sum warn; provision_build_inputs.sh parses
#  this file itself and has no such quirk).
#
# PROVENANCE of the recorded hashes (2026-07-09, RC rc-beta20260709):
#   - All six values computed directly from the operator's canonical main
#     checkout ( Claude Code\DCENT Projects) on
#     2026-07-09.
#   - stock_fpga_s9.bin / stock_fpga_extracted.bin additionally match the
#     2026-04-26 firmware-intake ledger
#     (
#      binary-hash-map.md) byte-for-byte — independent historical cross-check.
#   - The Linaro toolchain hash cee0087b... is the operator-ratified authentic
#     value, cross-verified against Buildroot's
#     toolchain-external-linaro-arm.hash at tags 2018.02 AND 2018.05
#     (upstream releases.linaro.org now 404s; see RC_BUILD_RUNBOOK.md
#     blocker #3). It matches TOOLCHAIN_SHA256_ARMHF in build_in_docker.sh.
#
# CONSUMERS (why each file is required):
#
#       s9 target: build_in_docker.sh Phase-0 sanity gate + Phase-4 staging;
#       package_sysupgrade.sh --board am1-s9 FIT kernel input. 2825904 bytes.
#
#       am2-s19jpro target: DCENT_AM2_S19J_KERNEL (build_in_docker.sh Phase 6
#       -> board post-image.sh probe). 2920448 bytes.
#
#       am2-s19jpro target: DCENT_AM2_S19J_BITSTREAM (BraiinsOS s9-io-am2
#       bitstream, live-proven). 2097152 bytes.
#   DCENT_OS_Antminer/dcentrald/pic-recovery/firmware/stock_fpga_s9.bin
#       Embedded at COMPILE TIME via include_bytes! in
#       pic-recovery/src/main.rs:791 — the whole dcentrald cargo workspace
#       fails to build without it (this was the first clean-checkout build
#       failure). Zynq-PCAP byte-swapped stock S9 FPGA image. 2438668 bytes.
#   DCENT_OS_Antminer/dcentrald/pic-recovery/firmware/stock_fpga_extracted.bin
#       Companion extracted-FPGA compare target kept alongside
#       stock_fpga_s9.bin (same gitignored firmware/ dir; recorded in the
#       2026-04-26 intake ledger). 2559264 bytes.
#   DCENT_OS_Antminer/buildroot/dl/toolchain-external-custom/gcc-linaro-...
#       Linaro GCC 7.2.1 armv7 external toolchain tarball (Buildroot
#       toolchain-external-custom). Upstream URL is DEAD (404) — this file
#       can ONLY come from the local cache / out-of-band bundle.
#       108376348 bytes.
#
# NOT in this manifest (already tracked in git — listed for completeness):
#         (tracked)
#   DCENT_OS_Antminer/dcentrald/dcentrald-api/assets/
#       stock-bitmain-manifest.json                                  (tracked)
#       stock-bitmain-manifest.json.sig      (tracked 0-byte placeholder;
#                                             real sig generated at tag time)
#
# =============================================================================

